<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98838833733795></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98838833733795><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98838833733795>RE: Wizards not nerfed</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98838833733795#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=42869><span id= >phynixice</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 27th 12:18 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Look, we all go through times that seem like we will never get to the next lvl but trust me it passes. <br> I'd like to put my 2cp into the AoE topic. AoE are very usefull in a good grp. When your tank pulls 2 to 4 mobs and you have 3 maybe 4 mellee types in grp they can engage 1 on 1 the mobs while you AoE the mobs to death with no chance of agro. I like to do this when the grp is getting steady yet boring exp to spice it up! It works very well for me. I must say that the dd AoE spells i like much better because the mobs dont have to stay in the area for an extended period of time.<br> <br><br>Phynix Spellfury<br>lvl 32 wizard<br>The Enhanced<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
